sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: It is extremely abnormal for svchost.exe to spawn without any CLI arguments and is normally observed when a malicious process spawns the process and injects code into the process memory space.

match_context.values: @{EventID=1; CommandLine="C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Host-process for services of Windows" dir=in action=allow program="C:\Windows\SysWOW64\svchost.exe" enable=yes>nul; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe}

@{EventID=1; Image=%windir%\System32\netsh.exe; CommandLine="%windir%\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Host-process for services of Windows" dir=in action=allow program="%windir%\SysWOW64\svchost.exe" enable=yes>nul}
